<P>
   TRIPP-LEWINSKY (Washington) _ For the first time since their
fateful friendship and taped conversations set off the
investigation of President Clinton, Monica Lewinsky and Linda Tripp
will confront each other again, this time in court. Ms. Lewinsky is
on the witness list for a pretrial hearing that is scheduled to
begin on Monday in Howard County, Maryland, where Ms. Tripp faces
charges that she illegally taped their telephone calls.
</P>
<P>
   ASIAN-AMERICAN-SPYING (Los Angeles) _ Asian American groups, who
have been relatively quiet in the past, explode with anger at the
arrest of Wen Ho Lee, citing racism and discrimination. Already a
legal defense fund is being formed and lawsuits are planned. By
James Sterngold.
</P>
<P>
   CALIF-ORANGE-COUNTY (Irvine, Calif.) _ Orange is the fifth
largest county in the nation, long a largely white enclave that
served as a bedroom to L.A. Now, it is changing, and is bitterly
divided over plans for a defunct, 4,000-acre military base near its
center, which has come to symbolize the war between the haves and
the have-less. By James Sterngold.
</P>
<P>
   MARS-RETHINK (Undated) _ After the failure of the Mars Polar
Lander and the mission that preceded it, scientists begin to
suggest that NASA's strategy of ``faster, cheaper, better'' may be
flawed. By William J. Broad.
</P>
