   MCMURTRY-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ Richard Bernstein reviews
``Walter Benjamin at the Dairy Queen,'' by Larry McMurtry (S&AMP;S).
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL  &LR;  (Coded f)
</P>
<P>
   ONLINE-ENTREPRENEURS (Undated) _ Among Wall Streeters whose
incomes once astounded Middle America, the mood has changed. Even
people in hot specialties bemoan the ``opportunity cost'' of
remaining a financier in the Internet age. Others are leaving to
join online start-ups, technology companies and venture capital
firms, the pillars of the new economy, where they sometimes take
home more than their old bosses from Day 1 _ and, they say, have
more fun. By Joseph Kahn.
</P>
<P>
   NEW-SLOT-MACHINES (Las Vegas) _ Slot machine makers are turning
to popular themes to make betting more entertaining and appealing
for those who are not dedicated gamblers. The trend worries
regulators and critics, who say that these new machines could
appeal to children, worsening the national problem of under-age
gambling. By Andrew Pollack.
</P>
<P>
   GOLDMAN-EUROPE (Undated) _ How Goldman Sachs has become the
telecom dealmaker in Europe. By Laura Holson.
</P>
<P>
   SUNDAY-TV-TALK (Undated) _ A shift of power on the
Sunday-morning TV talk show circuit. By Bill Carter.
</P>
<P>
   SATELLITE-TV (Undated) _ The new satellite TV legislation was
meant to give the satellite networks a more equal footing with
cable companies by giving satellite programmers the right to carry
local broadcast signals. But to the extent that this right becomes
an obligation, it may be economically unfeasible to carry out. By
Seth Schiesel.
</P>
