   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   ASIA-POLL _ WASHINGTON _ One-third of American adults and nearly
a quarter of college-bound high school students could not name the
ocean that separates the United States from Asia, according to a
new national poll by the New York-based Asia Society. The society
calls for schools to do a better job of teaching about Asia.
(Mollison, Cox News Service)
</P>
