   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-SYRIA _ JERUSALEM _ Predictions by Syria's foreign
minister Sunday that his country could make peace with Israel in
``a few months'' has raised Israeli expectations for the peace
talks scheduled to start this week. (Kaplow, Cox News Service)
MOVED
</P>
<P>
   SIERRA _ FREETOWN, Sierra Leone _ They are children, some as
young as 9 years old. Most have been abducted, then forced to fight
in a bitter and brutal civil war. Boys have been made to shoot
people with AK-47s and to cut off the hands of civilians, sometimes
members of their own families. Girls have been forced to be the
``wives'' of rebel soldiers, being raped at gunpoint, as one
14-year-old said in an interview, ``every day, every day.''
Sometimes, once these children escape the rebel force, their
families do not want them back. We look at the ways in which money
donated by Atlanta media mogul Ted Turner, through the U.N.
Foundation, is trying to get these kids back in school, get them
psychological care, negotiate their ways back into their villages
and families, and let them be kids once more. (Melvin, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). WITH (Melvin) PHOTOS. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
