the nation's major airlines are promising to treat you with a
little more kindness. Under pressure from Congress, which had
threatened legislative action, the air carriers came up with their
own customer service policies and asked lawmakers to give them a
chance to win back the affection of the public. The new policies
will begin Wednesday. (Hendricks, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
