<HEADER>
A6762 &Cx1f; tth-z
r v BC-BUDGET-SPI &LR;      12-12 0251
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BUDGET-SPI </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Monday, Dec. 13 and thereafter. If you have any questions, please
call Mary Downes on the national-foreign desk at (206) 448-8158.
</P>
<P>
   HOOD-INSTITUTE (Seattle) _ Dr. Leroy Hood, the University of
Washington scientist renowned for developing the technology that
has helped fuel the worldwide race to decipher the human genetic
code, is leaving the UW to start a private venture in Seattle. ``We
have a chance to change the way science is done,'' Hood said. ``I
want to create a model for how academic institutions will operate
in the future.''
</P>
<P>
   By Tom Paulson. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-SEAHAWKS-CHARGERS (Seattle) _ Seahawks vs. San Diego
Chargers.
</P>
<P>
   By Clare Farnsworth. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-THIEL-COLUMN (Seattle) _ Column from Seahawks-Chargers game.
</P>
<P>
   By Art Thiel. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-OWEN-COLUMN (Undated) _ I learned at an early age that
there were plenty of wonderful things to see and do in western
Canada. It was a wonderful place to visit, but you really wouldn't
want to eat there. Only lately, after numerous research excursions
north of the border, have I erased any prejudices to the point
where I might suggest that Vancouver may be the best restaurant
city north of San Francisco.
</P>
<P>
   By John Owen. (Story will move in the ``d'' category.)
