<HEADLINE>
SORRY, NO FREE SHAQ GIFT RAP
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Who says we don't know value when it hits us in
the puss?
</P>
<P>
   Top-five gift items available at Team L.A., the Office Max Depot
Center's superstore for stuff just outside the main gates of that
monument to downtown know-how:
</P>
<P>
   5. Lakers purple houndstooth boxer shorts ($20). Love to see
DRod in a pair of those. Oh, that's right....
</P>
<P>
   4. A 1:24 scale model Zamboni bank with the Kings' logo ($38).
Suitable for saving up cash for all that Stanley Cup gear that'll
come in around May.
</P>
<P>
   3. A distressed gray T-shirt with the ``Los Angeles'' script
from the Dodgers' road uniforms ($20). Distressed naturally after
going through last season.
</P>
<P>
   2. An assortment of L.A. Avengers shirts and hats (ridiculously
high prices vary). No jerseys? Hey, no team yet, kid.
</P>
<P>
   1. A Clippers' ``We're No. 1'' giant foam hand ($5). That's the
same price as a Kings', Lakers' or Dodgers' ``No. 1'' giant foam
hand, but which one provides more comic relief?...
</P>
<P>
   __The store also has plllllenty of Mo Taylor (23) and Mike
Olowokandi (34) tank tops. But nuthin' off the back of Lamar
Odom....
</P>
<P>
   __And don't pass up the half-off bin at the Dodger Stadium Top
of the Park shop _ !ital!puulenty of Raul Mondesi Collectibles to
be scooped up, we're told....
</P>
<P>
   __But all I want for Festivus is a deluxe recliner, if you're
wondering. A built-in cooler that holds six 12-ounce cans under one
arm rest. A telephone (with caller ID) under the other. And a
10-motor massage and heating system.
</P>
<P>
   It's the La-Z-Boy Oasis model (patent pending) for $899....
</P>
<P>
   __L.A.'s next shot at a pro football team _ the Spring Football
League, which wants to have games played in March through June.
L.A. has been mentioned as one of eight franchise cities, and Bo
Jackson has already staked claim to a team in Birmingham, Ala....
</P>
<P>
   __Proving news chicks dig the longball, Mark McGwire has been
playing long toss with our favorite KCBS Channel 2 anchor, the
fetchin' Gretchen Carr....
</P>
<P>
   __Peter Warrick, Heisman non-invitee in December, NFL top pick
in April....
</P>
