<P>
   __Just when ya think perpetual victim Steve Howe doesn't get
enough legal relief: Charged with drunk driving after a motorcycle
accident in 1997, which, by the way, he failed to report to
authorities until days later, he has filed a lawsuit in Montana
seeking damages against the utility company doing work on that road
at the time of his spill. Howe claims they left a 4-foot-wide
trench with inadequate warning lights....
</P>
<P>
   __Nuthin' quite more pathetic, either, than flipping on Court TV
to see the lawyer for Charlotte Hornets owner George Shinn admit
that his client is ``a sinner,'' but he never forced other women
into sex during adulterous relationships....
</P>
<P>
   __And a tearful buh-bye to Sir Chuck, whose quips we've learned
to file away for safe keeping. Such as being misquoted in his own
autobiography (``That was my fault, I should have read it before it
came out.''), and the popularity of ShaqDaddy (``The more attention
he gets, the less I have to deal with the nitwits in the media.'')
</P>
<P>
   Barkley's final bark as he was driven off in a golf cart with
